title: Retrieve the details of a single listing
description: Retrieves the details of a single listing.

path.name: listingId
path.description: The ID of the listing to retrieve.

enum.name: xml
enum.description: Serialize responses into XML.

enum.name: json
enum.description: Serialize responses into JSON.

query.name: increment_view_count
query.description: Indicates whether to increment the view count on the listing. Defaults to true.

query.name: question_limit
query.description: The maximum number of questions and answers to return. Defaults to unlimited.

query.name: return_member_profile
query.description: If true also returns the member's public profile information. Defaults to false.

query.name: return_variants
query.description: If true, returns full details of all variants in the VariantDefinition field. Only applies to MVL listings.

query.name: rsqid
query.description: The referring search query ID; used to link requests to searches for analytics purposes. Optional.

fields.name: ListingId
fields.description: The ID of the listing.

fields.name: Title
fields.description: The listing title.

fields.name: Category
fields.description: The listing category.

fields.name: StartPrice
fields.description: The start price.

fields.name: BuyNowPrice
fields.description: The Buy Now price.

fields.name: StartDate
fields.description: The date the listing was created.

fields.name: EndDate
fields.description: The date the listing will end.

fields.name: IsFeatured
fields.description: Is this a featured listing?

fields.name: HasGallery
fields.description: Is this a gallery listing?

fields.name: IsBold
fields.description: Is this a bold listing?

fields.name: IsHighlighted
fields.description: Is this a highlighted listing?

fields.name: HasHomePageFeature
fields.description: Is this a homepage feature listing?

fields.name: BidderAndWatchers
fields.description: The number of bidders and watcher for this listing.

fields.name: MaxBidAmount
fields.description: The current leading bid amount.

fields.name: AsAt
fields.description: The date and time the response was generated on the server.

fields.name: CategoryPath
fields.description: The category path.

fields.name: PhotoId
fields.description: The ID of the primary photo for the listing (if the listing has a photo).

fields.name: HasPayNow
fields.description: Indicates whether the item has Pay Now.

fields.name: IsNew
fields.description: Indicates whether the item is marked as new.

fields.name: RegionId
fields.description:
The ID of the region where this item is located. In the general search, listing details and watchlist APIs this is the ID of the seller's region (using the two-tier region/suburb system), which means it might be inconsistent with the region name. In the property search API this is the ID of the property region, using the three-tier region/district/suburb system.

                                This field cannot cope with the two main geographical classification systems.  Except for the property search API, it should not be used.

fields.name: Region
fields.description: The name of the region where this item is located.

fields.name: SuburbId
fields.description: The ID of the suburb where this item is located. Only populated by the property search API, which means it uses the three-tier region/district/suburb system.

fields.name: Suburb
fields.description: The name of the suburb where this item is located.

fields.name: PickupLocality
fields.description: The pick-up location details if pick-up is allowed and has been specified.

nested_fields.description: The pickup suburb.
The pickup district.
The pickup region.

fields.name: BidCount
fields.description: The number of bids on the item.

fields.name: ViewCount
fields.description: The number of times the listing has been viewed.

fields.name: IsReserveMet
fields.description: Indicates whether the item's reserve has been met.

fields.name: HasReserve
fields.description: Indicates whether the item has a reserve.

fields.name: HasBuyNow
fields.description: Indicates whether the item has Buy Now.

fields.name: NoteDate
fields.description: The date of the note on an item.

fields.name: CategoryName
fields.description: The display name of the category.

fields.name: ReserveState
fields.description: The flag to display on an item.

enum.name: None
enum.description: There is no reserve on the item (i.e. the reserve price is the same as the starting price).

enum.name: Met
enum.description: The value of the highest bid has exceeded the reserve price.

enum.name: NotMet
enum.description: The value of the highest bid has not reached the reserve price.

enum.name: NotApplicable
enum.description: The listing cannot have a reserve because bidding is not allowed. This may be because it is a classified or because it is a Buy Now Only auction.

fields.name: Attributes
fields.description: The attributes for the item that are intended to be displayed on the UI.

nested_fields.description: A name which uniquely identifies the attribute. Required when selling or editing.
The name of the attribute, in a form suitable for displaying to users. Not required when selling or editing.

The string value of the attribute. When listing, the valid values for the attribute can be determined using the "Retrieve attributes for a category" API. Use "false" or "true" for boolean attributes. Required when selling or editing.
The type of the attribute, which determines the range of acceptable values. Not required when selling or editing.

enum_values.name: Boolean
enum_values.description: The attribute value is a boolean (true/false).

enum_values.name: Integer
enum_values.description: The attribute value is an integer.

enum_values.name: Decimal
enum_values.description: The attribute value is a floating point number.

enum_values.name: String
enum_values.description: The attribute value can be arbitrary text.

enum_values.name: DateTime
enum_values.description: The attribute value is a date & time (in UTC).

nested_fields.description: The allowed range of the attribute. Only applies to numeric attributes. Not required when selling or editing.
A list of options, if the attribute is restricted to a fixed set of values. Not required when selling or editing.
Indicates whether the attribute must be present when selling an item.
The value of the attribute as it needs to be displayed to the end users

fields.name: HiddenAttributes
fields.description: The attributes for the item that are not intended to be displayed on the UI.

fields.name: IsClassified
fields.description: Indicates whether the item is a classified.

fields.name: OpenHomes
fields.description: A collection of open home times for this listing. Only applies to open home listings.

nested_fields.description: The date and time the open home is open for viewing. The date must be in the future and it must be less than 56 days from the current date. Specify dates in the UTC time zone.
The date and time the open home is no longer open for viewing. Must be the same day asStart.

fields.name: RelistedItemId
fields.description: The ID of the new listing if this listing was relisted.

fields.name: Subtitle
fields.description: The subtitle, if present.

fields.name: ReservePrice
fields.description: The reserve price for the auction. This is available in the sold/unsold items APIs and, if you are the seller, the listing details API.

fields.name: IsBuyNowOnly
fields.description: Indicates whether or not this is a Buy Now Only listing.

fields.name: HasMultiple
fields.description: Indicates whether there is more than one item available. Only applicable for Buy Now Only listings.

fields.name: Quantity
fields.description: The total quantity available of the item. Only applicable for Buy Now Only listings. When retrieving won items this value represents the number sold, not the total quantity. When retrieving sold items, this value is not present (use QuantitySold instead). When retrieving listing details, this value is only present if you are the seller.

fields.name: IsFlatShippingCharge
fields.description: Indicates whether one flat shipping fee will be charged if more than one of this item is purchased. Only applicable for Buy Now Only listings.

fields.name: RemainingGalleryPlusRelists
fields.description: The number of times the item can be relisted and get the gallery promotion for free. This value is only present if you are the seller and the listing had the gallery promotion applied due to the gallery plus promotion. Note that for this field, a value of zero is not the same as if the field is missing (a value of zero means gallery plus is in effect whereas if the field is missing it means that you are not the seller or gallery plus is not in effect).

fields.name: MinimumNextBidAmount
fields.description: The smallest amount that will be accepted for the next bid. Only applicable to auctions which allow bidding (i.e. not classifieds and not Buy Now Only auctions). You must still check for the "bid too small" error when using this value, as someone may make a bid after you have checked this value but before you have finished placing your bid.

fields.name: IsOnWatchList
fields.description: Indicates whether the item is on the authenticated member's watchlist.

fields.name: WatchlistReminder
fields.description: If the item is on the watchlist, it indicates the user's preference of when they should get watchlist emails for the item.

enum.name: None
enum.description: No emails for watchlist items.

enum.name: OneHourBefore
enum.description: One hour before the listing closes.

enum.name: TwelveHoursBefore
enum.description: Twelve hours before the listing closes.

enum.name: TwentyFourHoursBefore
enum.description: Twenty hours before the listing closes.

fields.name: GeographicLocation
fields.description: The geographic location (latitude and longitude) of a property.

nested_fields.description: The latitude of the location, in degrees (WGS84).
The longitude of the location, in degrees (WGS84).
The northing of the location, in metres (NZTM).
The easting of the location, in metres (NZTM).
The accuracy of the geographic location (address, street or suburb).

enum_values.name: None
enum_values.description: The accuracy of the geographic location is not known.

enum_values.name: Address
enum_values.description: The geographic location is accurate to the address level.

enum_values.name: Street
enum_values.description: The geographic location is accurate to the street level.

enum_values.name: Suburb
enum_values.description: The geographic location is accurate to the suburb level.

enum_values.name: AdminPinpoint
enum_values.description: The geographic location is accurate to the AdminPinPoint level.

fields.name: PriceDisplay
fields.description: The price, in a format suitable for displaying to the user. Some categories may have special pricing rules, e.g. properties may have "Price by negotiation".

fields.name: TotalReviewCount
fields.description: The total number of user-submitted reviews. Currently only applies to services listings.

fields.name: PositiveReviewCount
fields.description: The number of user-submitted reviews which are positive (i.e. the user selected the thumbs up graphic when submitting a review). Currently only applies to services listings.

fields.name: SendPaymentInstructions
fields.description: Indicates whether payment instructions are automatically sent to buyers. This value is only present if you are the seller.

fields.name: CanUsePayNowInstant
fields.description: Indicates whether the PayNowInstant is available for this listing.

fields.name: ExternalReferenceId
fields.description: The external reference ID, if one exists. Only available to the seller of a listing.

fields.name: HasAppliedForJob
fields.description: Indicates whether the authenticated member has applied for the job. Only applies for job listings.

fields.name: JobApplicationDate
fields.description: The date and time of the member's most recent job application, if any. This field will only be populated if HasAppliedForJob is true.

fields.name: SKU
fields.description: SKU or Stock Keeping Unit. Used to uniquely identify an auction's product line.

fields.name: IsClearance
fields.description: This indicates that the listing is a clearance item. Clearance listings include listings with was/now pricing and general clearance stock.

fields.name: WasPrice
fields.description: The usual price that a product is sold at, or the price before it was marked down. This is always more than the Buy Now price for Auctions, or more than the asking price for Classifieds.This field will only be populated if IsClearance is true.

fields.name: PercentageOff
fields.description: The percentage that a product has been discounted. This has been rounded for display purposes. This field will only be populated if IsClearance is true.

fields.name: Branding
fields.description: A list of branding images associated with this listing.

nested_fields.description: A large square branding image with dimensions of 480x480.
A large rectangular branding image with dimensions of 480x200.
Banner outline/stroke colour, tick the checkbox before saving to apply the new colour
Banner background colour, tick the checkbox before saving to apply the new colour
Banner text colour, tick the checkbox before saving to apply the new colour
Disable the agent branding regardless of Super Feature status
The name of the office location
The url of a larger version of the logo

fields.name: OfferStatus
fields.description: The status of the fixed price offer for this listing (if there is one). Only available if you are the seller or a recipient of the offer.

enum.name: None
enum.description: A fixed price offer has not been created for this listing, or you are not the seller or a recipient and so no information is available.

enum.name: Active
enum.description: A fixed price offer is currently active. The PendingOffer field will contain details of the offer. If PendingOffer is unavailable, seeFixed Price Offer Methodsfor more information.

enum.name: Withdrawn
enum.description: A fixed price offer was created, but then was withdrawn by the seller. The ClosedOffer field will contain details of the offer. If ClosedOffer is unavailable, seeFixed Price Offer Methodsfor more information.

enum.name: Expired
enum.description: A fixed price offer was created, but time ran out before all the recipients could respond. The ClosedOffer field will contain details of the offer. If ClosedOffer is unavailable, seeFixed Price Offer Methodsfor more information.

enum.name: Declined
enum.description: The fixed price offer was declined by all the recipients. The ClosedOffer field will contain details of the offer. If ClosedOffer is unavailable, seeFixed Price Offer Methodsfor more information.

enum.name: Accepted
enum.description: The fixed price offer was accepted. The ClosedOffer field will contain details of the offer. If ClosedOffer is unavailable, seeFixed Price Offer Methodsfor more information.
